Hello there, moparscape community.

Today, I am releasing my little jQuery slideshow script. Everything is 100% made by me besides two plugins.

CSS Code:
[code=css]
/*
	@Author: Robby;
*/
#base{
	width: 300px;
	margin: 0px auto;
}
#slideshow{
	float: left;
	width: 100px;
	margin: 0px auto;
}
#slideshow img{
	background-color: #f0f0f0;
	padding: 10px;
	width: 100px;
	height: 100px;
}
#prev{
	float: left;
	padding-top: 30px;
	width: 64px;
}
#prev:hover{
	cursor: hand;
}
#next{
	float: right;
	padding-top: 30px;
	width: 64px;
}
#next:hover{
	cursor: hand;
}
[/code]

jQuery Code:
[code=javascript]
$(document).ready(function(){
	$("#slideshow").cycle({
	fx: 'fade',
	speed: 'slow',
	timeout: 5000,
	next: '#next',
	prev: '#prev'
	});
});
[/code]

MUST INCLUDE PLUGINS!

<script src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.8.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="http://cloud.github.com/downloads/malsup/cycle/jquery.cycle.all.latest.js"></script>

If you aren't sure how to set this up, post a comment and I'll be glad to help.

Thanks for reading,
Sibor aka Robby

PS: I will continue to update this - slideshow - until the point it is 100% perfect!
